<a name="0">[0]</a> <a href="#0" id=0>(9) Emerging a semantic image according to a given network in the physical space or socio space.</a>
<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>(11) Linking a semantic image to a language unit defined in the symbol space.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>zoom-in to emerge the specific semantic image, and zoom-out to emerge a more general semantic image.</a>
<a name="3">[3]</a> <a href="#3" id=3>zoom-in to emerge the small-scale semantic image, and zoom-out to emerge the large-scale semantic image.</a>
<a name="4">[4]</a> <a href="#4" id=4>The mental space can adapt its structure with continuously emerging semantic images and complex reasoning.</a>
<a name="5">[5]</a> <a href="#5" id=5>The mental space can compose semantic images and externalize it through various languages.</a>
<a name="6">[6]</a> <a href="#6" id=6>(8) Analogizing a point or a semantic link to the similar points or semantic links.</a>
<a name="7">[7]</a> <a href="#7" id=7>(3) It can emerge more causes (in multiple spaces) from an effect, and emerge more effects (in multiple spaces) from a cause with the development of the complex space.</a>
<a name="8">[8]</a> <a href="#8" id=8>Semantic worldviews influence the structure of the mental space and its evolution.</a>
<a name="9">[9]</a> <a href="#9" id=9>One point can link to the other points with certain semantics and probabilities to render semantic images.</a>
<a name="10">[10]</a> <a href="#10" id=10>Imagination is the ability and process of linking one semantic image to the other, or significantly extending semantic images by complex reasoning.</a>
<a name="11">[11]</a> <a href="#11" id=11>The process of painting concerns the process of experiencing, emerging, reasoning, evolving and externalizing semantic images.</a>
<a name="12">[12]</a> <a href="#12" id=12>Writing can be regarded as a process of selecting and organizing the appropriate language units corresponding to the semantic image emerged in mind.</a>
<a name="13">[13]</a> <a href="#13" id=13>(1) Selecting the situation for reflection according to the active points in the mental space reflecting the physical, physiological, psychological, and socio requirements.</a>
<a name="14">[14]</a> <a href="#14" id=14>(3) Moving the instances in one point to another point according to the change of the structure of the space.</a>
